<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When I create a list of credentials in Windows machine, my file has \r at the end of each line</p>

<p>When this file later is parsed on Linux server, every password has \r at the end. And authentication fails.</p>

<p>I suggest to change line 158 in Zend_Auth_Adapter_Http_Resolver_File to this line:</p>

<pre><code>            $password = rtrim($line[2], "\r");
</code></pre>

<p>This will resolve the problem and won't hurt existing users. I can't imagine that anyone may have a password with \r at the end.</p>

